  ],
  "text": "Successfully unified both positioning axes (X and Y) to support the same pattern: special cases and percentage values. Now both data-position-x and data-position-y work consistently:\n\n- Special cases: \"body-center\", \"cell-center\", \"above-body\", \"between-body-eyes\"  \n- Percentage values: \"25%\", \"50%\", \"75%\" etc. for precise positioning\n\nThe implementation uses the same pattern for both axes - checking for endswith(\"%\") to distinguish percentage values from special cases. This creates a consistent, intuitive API that's easy to document and use.\n\nNo changes were needed to existing hair SVG files since they already use special cases that remain supported.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
